pageContext.claim: “You know, we just put something up yesterday on Google--where they were promoting Obama, Obama, Obama -- the day I got to office for the same event, which was the State of the Union speech, the day I got to office, they -- it was like, dead.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump had posted a video on Twitter that purported to show how Google promoted the State of the Union address when Obama was president but not when Trump was president. But the video was fake; Google did promote Trump's 2018 State of the Union. "We have historically not promoted the first address to Congress by a new President, which is technically not a State of the Union address. As a result, we didn’t include a promotion on google.com for this address in either 2009 or 2017," Google said in a statement.
